Package: lbm2r
Title: Read and Write MSDIAL LBM2 Lipid Database Files
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Rico", "Derks", , role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "r.j.e.derks@lumc.nl")
Description: Provides functions to read and write the binary LBM2 format used
    by MS-DIAL as its in-silico lipid MS/MS spectral library. The LBM2 format
    stores lipid records serialized with MessagePack and compressed with LZ4.
    Each record contains compound metadata (name, formula, SMILES, InChIKey,
    adduct, retention time, collision cross-section, etc.) and the associated
    MS/MS peak list. This package allows users to inspect, modify, and create
    LBM2 databases entirely within R.
